===2020 census===
As of the [[census]] of 2020, there were 8,059 people residing in the town. There were 3,774 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|racial makeup]] of the town was 83.6% [[Non-Hispanic whites|White]], 7.2% [[African Americans|African American or Black]], 0.2% [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian]], 1.2% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.0% [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 1.4% from other races, and 6.4% from [[Multiracial Americans|two or more races]]. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 3.6% of the population.

===2010 census===
As of the census<ref name="GR2" /> of 2010, there were 8,092 people, 3,774 housing units, and 3,547 households in the town. The racial makeup of the town was 90.0% White, 5.6% African American, 0.1% Native American, 1.0% Asian, 0.0% Pacific Islander, 1.3% from other races, and 2.0% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 2.8% of the population. The median income for a household in the town was $44,667.

